      <hedline>
        <hl1>Boorishness Knows No Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard S Reade letter responds to Peter Applebome's July 30 column on loud, obscene rap music being played by man at gas pump (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The poignant ''Opinion'' by Mr. Applebome shows two things:</p>
        <p>* The things we regret most in life are those things we did not do.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The poignant ''Opinion'' by Mr. Applebome shows two things:</p>
        <p>* The things we regret most in life are those things we did not do.</p>
        <p>* Mainstream journalists who live in upscale communities have lost touch with the real world.</p>
        <p>The answer to the question ''What Would You Have Done'' is: I'd politely ask the offender to lower the volume. Failing that, I'd note his plate number and report him to his supervisor at the prison where he works.</p>
        <p>RICHARD S. READE  Setauket</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
